    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Divus Augustus parens <lb n="2"/>dedit <lb n="3"/><del rend="erasure">[<expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Caesar</del>] Augustus <lb n="4"/>Germanicus <del rend="erasure">[<expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ater</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>atriae</ex></expan></del>] <lb n="5"/>refecit <lb n="6"/>in huius balinei <expan><abbr>lavation</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> HS CCCC <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>nomin</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>ai</ex></expan> Aviasi <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ili</ex></expan> Senecae <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ili</ex></expan> sui <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan> Aviasius Servandus <lb n="8"/>pater <expan><abbr>testament</abbr><ex>o</ex></expan> legavit ut ex reditu eius <expan><abbr>summ</abbr><ex>ae</ex></expan> <lb n="9"/>in perpetuum viri et impuberes <expan><abbr>utriusq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> sexus <lb n="10"/>gratis laventur
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Horster: mehrfache, voneinander abweichende Textwiedergaben. Datierung bezieht sich auf Z. 1-5; Z. 6-10 wurden nachträglich eingemeißelt (wohl im 2. Jh. n. Chr.).</p>
            </div>
